  "The heat source is too strong and should be turned down to a lower setting now": "",
  "Pure water is evaporating normally since water temperature fluctuates when boiling": "",
  "A fluctuating temperature indicates that multiple substances are evaporating simultaneously. A steady temperature reading means a single pure substance is boiling at its boiling point.": "",
  "A camping guide needs to purify dirty pond water in the field. They boil the water and collect the steam on a cold metal plate. What technique are they using?": "",
  "Filtration, because the steam passes through the air like a filter and particles stay behind": "",
  "Distillation, because they are evaporating water and condensing it on a cold surface": "",
  "Chromatography, because the water travels along the metal plate and separates impurities": "",
  "Crystallization, because impurities form crystals on the cold metal plate from the steam": "",
  "This is a simple form of distillation. The water evaporates (leaving impurities behind), the steam condenses on the cold plate, and the collected water is much purer.": "",
  "Why does distillation produce purer water than simple evaporation when starting with saltwater?": "",
  "Evaporation and distillation produce the exact same result every time with no difference": "",
